    "body": "Yes, [Linux](https://linux.die.net/man/3/posix_fallocate), [FreeBSD](https://www.freebsd.org/cgi/man.cgi?query=posix_fallocate) and [NetBSD](https://netbsd.gw.com/cgi-bin/man-cgi?posix_fallocate++NetBSD-current) have `posix_fallocate()` (maybe others too). The types and semantics of the arguments and return value are the same on all.\r\n\r\nI am a bit surprised that MacOS and OpenBSD do not have it. The code handles MacOS separately anyway.\r\n\r\nThanks!",
