    "body": "`_POSIX_C_SOURCE` is not Linux or GCC specific. However, only the [Linux man page](https://linux.die.net/man/3/posix_fallocate) for `posix_fallocate()` mentions it as a requirement. [FreeBSD](https://www.freebsd.org/cgi/man.cgi?query=posix_fallocate) and [NetBSD](https://netbsd.gw.com/cgi-bin/man-cgi?posix_fallocate++NetBSD-current) man pages don't, implying that the function is available without having to define `_POSIX_C_SOURCE` to a specific value.\r\n\r\nIn any case, this is what the source code in [src/util/system.cpp already does](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/src/util/system.cpp#L21-L29) and it's important to have the check and source code do the same thing.",
